    "A 20,000-patient trial reports a new drug cuts myocardial infarction with a relative risk of 0.80 and a 95% confidence interval of 0.62 to 1.03. A journalist's headline reads: \"Trial proves the drug does not work.\" A cardiologist objects. What is the most accurate interpretation?",
